eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 0 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.

Impairment of gastrointestinal function or gastrointestinal disease that may significantly alter the absorption of RAD001 (e.g., ulcerative disease, uncontrolled nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, malabsorption syndrome or small bowel resection)

groups.description: Participants undergo FDG-labeled standard PET/CT scan followed by FDG-labeled 4D respiratory-gated PET/CT scan at baseline and at 4-8 weeks after completion of radiation therapy.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Diagnostic (radiation therapy planning)

groups.description: Arm I (usual care): Self-help materials and brief relapse prevention advice based on Treating Tobacco Use and Dependence Clinical Practice Guideline.
groups.name: Smoking Prevention Usual Care

outcome_measures.analysis_method: The proportion of disagreements across all time points will be estimated with an intercept-only GEE regression model that accounts for correlation among measures from the same patient. This proportion will be reported with a 95% confidence interval.
outcome_measures.measure: Frequency with which CT and qualitative FDG-PET disagree in their classifications of response

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Kaplan-Meier estimates of PFS rates will be calculated, along with their corresponding 95% confidence intervals. The median, 12-month, and 24-month PFS rates will be estimated.
outcome_measures.time_frame: Time from start treatment to time of progression or death, whichever occurs first, assessed up to 24 months

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Compared for isolated CNS, isolated bone marrow, and combined bone marrow relapse between IR patients on the non-bortezomib containing arm on this study (no CRT) with similar patients on AALL0434 (+ CRT).
